wobani.core

Class GameObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • wobani.core.GameObject

  • public class GameObject
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents an entity which has it's own position, Mesh or any other properties, you should create a new GameObject. A GameObjct can store any number of Components, including Cameras, Meshes, Splines, Materials, light sources etc. Of course you can create youe own Component. It also offers parent-child relations between GameObjectContainer.
    See Also:
    Component
